**Product Requirements Document (PRD)**  
**USFinNexus.com**  
**Free Mortgage & Finance Calculators Hub**  

**Version:** 1.0  
**Date:** February 22, 2026  
**Author:** Prepared for Rajveer (Developer & Founder)  
**Status:** Ready for Designer/Agent Implementation  

---

### 1. Executive Summary  
USFinNexus.com is a clean, fast, trustworthy web platform offering **100% free** mortgage and personal finance calculators focused on everyday American users.  

The core MVP launches with a **Mortgage Calculator Hub** (including affordability, refinance, auto/personal loans) that matches or exceeds competitors like Bankrate, Zillow, NerdWallet, and MortgageCalculator.org in accuracy and depth — but with one massive differentiator: **instant, no-signup, no-email PDF + CSV full reports** that users can download in one click.  

**Goal:** Become the go-to bookmark for Americans checking mortgage scenarios daily (3.4M+ monthly US searches for “mortgage calculator” alone). Monetize via high-CPM Google AdSense (finance niche: $20–50 RPM) while building sticky users for future premium cloud saves.  

**Launch in 7–14 days** as a developer-built Next.js site on USFinNexus.com.  

**Expected 90-day outcome:** 20k–100k monthly US visitors → $500–3,000 AdSense + viral shares from free downloads.  

---

### 2. Product Vision & Objectives  
**Vision:** The cleanest, most useful, spam-free finance calculator experience on the internet — built for real Americans who hate popups, email captures, and lender spam.  

**Business Objectives:**  
- Rank #1–3 on Google for “free mortgage calculator 2026”, “mortgage calculator with PDF download”, “how much house can I afford calculator”.  
- Achieve 5+ min average session time (longer than Bankrate/Zillow).  
- 8–15% conversion to repeat visits via local saves + share links.  
- Zero aggressive lead-gen (no “get pre-qualified” popups on free calcs).  

**User Objectives:**  
- Get instant, accurate numbers for home buying/refinancing/budgeting.  
- Export full professional reports for realtors, lenders, or spouses without hassle.  
- Feel trusted (big disclaimers, no data collection).  

---

### 3. Target Audience & User Personas  
**Primary Audience:**  
- 25–55 year old Americans (home buyers, refinancers, first-time buyers, homeowners).  
- High-intent searchers: “monthly mortgage payment calculator”, “mortgage affordability 2026”.  
- 60% mobile, 40% desktop (evening/weekend usage spikes).  

**Key Personas:**  
1. **Alex, 32, First-Time Buyer** (Tech-savvy, Reddit user) – Wants affordability + PDF to show spouse/realtor.  
2. **Sarah, 45, Refinancer** (Busy mom) – Compares current vs new rate, downloads CSV for Excel.  
3. **Mike, 38, Homeowner** (Budget-conscious) – Uses extra payments + amortization to plan payoff.  

---

### 4. Competitor Analysis (Feb 22, 2026 Research)  
Top players all offer core PITI calculations but fail on user friction:

- **Bankrate.com** → Strong ZIP-based taxes/insurance, amortization tab, extra payments, heavy lender lead-gen, **no PDF/CSV**.  
- **Zillow.com** → Loan-type selector (FHA/VA), interactive schedule graph, pre-qual buttons, **no downloads**.  
- **NerdWallet** → Detailed amortization table, total interest/payoff date, lender comparisons, **no exports**.  
- **MortgageCalculator.org** → Donut charts, bi-weekly, points calculator, printer-friendly only, **no clean PDF**.  

**Market Gap You Own:**  
- Instant full-report PDF (summary + tables + charts) and CSV without email/signup.  
- No forced lender quotes on calculator pages.  
- Modern, dark-mode-ready, lightning-fast UI.  

---

### 5. Key Features & Requirements  

#### 5.1 Core Calculators (All 100% Free, Live-Updating)  
**Main Mortgage Calculator** (Homepage + dedicated page):  
- Inputs: Home price, down payment ($, %), interest rate, loan term (10/15/20/30 yr + custom), ZIP code (for tax/insurance estimates), property tax (annual), homeowners insurance (annual), HOA (monthly), PMI (auto or manual), start date.  
- Outputs: Total monthly payment, full PITI breakdown, principal & interest only, total interest paid, payoff date, total payments.  
- Tabs/Sections: Breakdown | Amortization Schedule | Extra Payments | Charts.  

**Additional Interconnected Calculators** (Top nav + sidebar links):  
- How Much House Can I Afford? (income, debts, DTI, credit score estimate).  
- Refinance Savings & Break-Even.  
- Auto Loan Calculator.  
- Personal Loan/Debt Payoff.  
- Side-by-Side Loan Comparison (up to 3 scenarios).  

#### 5.2 Unique & Differentiating Features (Your Killer Edge)  
- **Instant Free Downloads** (big green buttons above/below results):  
  - Full PDF Report (5–10 pages: cover with site logo, all inputs/outputs, amortization table, charts as images, professional disclaimer).  
  - CSV/Excel-ready export (full amortization data).  
- **Local Scenario Saves** (10 named saves using browser storage: “Austin Home 2026”, “Refi Option A”).  
- **One-Click Shareable Link** (pre-fills all fields in URL).  
- **Rent vs Buy Comparator**.  
- **Mortgage Points Buy-Down**.  
- **Inflation-Adjusted Payments Toggle**.  
- **PWA** (Add to Home Screen button for app-like feel).  

#### 5.3 Shared / Delight Features (Across All Pages)  
- Live sliders + number inputs with real-time updates.  
- Interactive charts: Balance-over-time line + payment breakdown pie.  
- Full amortization table (monthly/yearly toggle, filter, 360 rows).  
- Extra payments simulator (one-time + recurring + bi-weekly).  
- Mobile-first responsive design.  
- Dark/light mode toggle.  
- Print-friendly view.  

---

### 6. User Flows & Page Specifications  
**Homepage:** Hero with main mortgage calc + “Try Affordability” + “See All Tools” cards.  
**Calculator Pages:** Clean single-focus layout (left: inputs, right: results + charts). Sticky download buttons.  
**Blog/Resources:** 15+ SEO articles (e.g., “Best Free Mortgage Calculator 2026”).  
**Footer:** All calculators, disclaimers, privacy (no tracking beyond analytics).  

---

### 7. UI/UX Design Guidelines (2026 Finance Trends)  
- **Color Palette:** Navy blue (#0A2540) primary, Green accents (#00C853) for success/CTAs, clean white/gray cards.  
- **Typography:** Modern sans-serif (Inter or System), large readable numbers for payments.  
- **Trust Elements:** Big red disclaimer banner on every calc: “For estimation only. Not financial, tax, or legal advice. Consult professionals.” + SSL badge.  
- **Style:** Minimal, whitespace-heavy, subtle shadows, professional yet approachable (like upgraded Bankrate but cleaner).  
- **Accessibility:** WCAG 2.2 AA, high contrast, keyboard navigation.  

---

### 8. Technical Requirements (High-Level for Developer)  
- Next.js (App Router) + Tailwind + shadcn/ui + Recharts.  
- 100% client-side math (no backend for MVP).  
- Vercel hosting + custom domain USFinNexus.com.  
- Google AdSense integration (non-intrusive banners).  
- Future: Easy plug-in for Supabase (user accounts).  

---

### 9. Monetization Strategy  
- **Primary:** Google AdSense on all pages (high-CPM finance).  
- **Secondary (Month 2+):** Premium subscription ($4.99/mo) for cloud saves, unlimited history, ad-free, branded PDFs.  
- No paywalls on core features.  

---

### 10. SEO & Marketing Requirements  
- SEO-optimized page titles/meta (e.g., “Free Mortgage Calculator 2026 with PDF Download | USFinNexus”).  
- Blog with 20+ targeted posts.  
- Submit to Google Search Console Day 1.  
- Share on Reddit (r/personalfinance, r/RealEstate), Facebook groups.  

---

### 11. Success Metrics & KPIs  
- Monthly unique visitors: 50k+ by Month 3.  
- Average session duration: >4 minutes.  
- Download rate: 15%+ of users.  
- Bounce rate: <45%.  
- AdSense revenue tracking.  

---

### 12. Roadmap  
**Phase 1 (MVP – Launch Week):** Mortgage + Affordability + Downloads + Local Save.  
**Phase 2 (Week 3):** Refinance, Auto Loan, Blog launch.  
**Phase 3 (Month 2):** Premium subscription + more calculators.  

---

### 13. Legal & Disclaimers  
- Prominent disclaimers on every page and in every PDF.  
- Privacy policy: Minimal data collection.  
- Terms: “Estimates only”.  

---

### 14. Assumptions & Risks  
- Users value clean experience over lender quotes.  
- Finance CPM remains high in 2026.  
- Risk: Google algorithm changes — mitigated by multiple high-quality pages.  

---

