Development Product Requirements Document (Technical PRD)
USFinNexus.com
Free Mortgage & Personal Finance Calculators Hub
Version: 1.0 (Development-Focused)
Date: February 22, 2026
Prepared for: Rajveer (Lead Developer)
Status: Ready for Implementation
1. Executive Summary & Product Goals
USFinNexus.com is a 100% client-side, high-performance, SEO-optimized web application delivering professional-grade mortgage and finance calculators.
Core Differentiator (2026 Market Gap): Instant, no-signup, no-email PDF + CSV full reports with charts/tables — something Bankrate, Zillow, and NerdWallet do not offer freely.
Technical Goals:
Zero backend/server costs for MVP (pure client-side math + browser APIs).
Sub-1s load time, 100 Lighthouse scores (mobile/desktop).
Full SSR/SSG for SEO (target top 3 Google rankings for “free mortgage calculator 2026 with PDF”).
Scalable to 100k+ monthly US visitors on Vercel free/hobby tier.
Easy future plug-in for premium (Supabase auth/DB).
Launch Timeline: MVP live in 7–10 days (you as solo dev).
2. Tech Stack (2026 Best-Practice Selection)
Frontend Framework: Next.js 16 (App Router + React 19) – SSR/SSG for SEO, streaming, partial prerendering.
Language: TypeScript 5.7+ (strict mode).
Styling: Tailwind CSS 4 + shadcn/ui (component library) + clsx/tailwind-merge.
Charts: Recharts 2.15+ (Line, Pie, ResponsiveContainer – client-side only).
Forms & Validation: react-hook-form 7.55 + zod 3.24 (schema validation).
PDF Generation: jsPDF 3.0+ + html2canvas 1.4+ (capture DOM section → high-quality PDF with charts).
CSV Export: Native Blob + URL.createObjectURL (no extra lib).
Icons: lucide-react 0.475+.
State Management: React useState/useReducer + URLSearchParams (for shareable links) + localStorage (scenario saves).
PWA: Next-PWA or manual manifest/service worker (optional but recommended).
Analytics: Vercel Analytics + Google Analytics 4 (minimal, privacy-first).
AdSense: Google AdSense script (non-intrusive placement via next/script).
Testing: Jest + React Testing Library + Playwright (E2E).
Linting/Formatting: ESLint + Prettier + Husky.
Deployment: Vercel (zero-config, custom domain USFinNexus.com, free SSL, edge functions if needed later).
Why this stack? Matches 90%+ of active open-source Next.js mortgage/EMI calculators on GitHub (2025–2026 repos) and delivers Bankrate-level UX with zero server cost.
3. System Architecture
100% Client-Side MVP: All calculations run in browser (no API routes, no DB, no Node server).
Data Flow:
User inputs → React state → Real-time recalculation (useEffect on every change) → Render results/charts → On “Download” → html2canvas captures result card/table/chart → jsPDF assembles multi-page PDF.
Sharing: Serialize form state to URL query params (e.g., /?homePrice=350000&rate=6.8...).
Local Saves: JSON array in localStorage (max 10 named scenarios).
Future Backend (Phase 3): Optional Supabase (Postgres + Auth) – swap localStorage → Supabase client.
Security/Privacy: No data leaves browser. Big disclaimers everywhere + privacy policy page.
4. Folder Structure (Recommended)
/app
  /calculators
    /mortgage/page.tsx
    /affordability/page.tsx
    /refinance/page.tsx
    /auto-loan/page.tsx
  /blog
    /[slug]/page.tsx
  /components
    /ui/               ← shadcn components
    CalculatorForm.tsx
    ResultsPanel.tsx
    AmortizationTable.tsx
    DownloadButtons.tsx
    ScenarioSaver.tsx
  /lib
    formulas.ts        ← all pure math functions
    pdfGenerator.ts
    csvExporter.ts
    taxEstimates.ts    ← static ZIP/state averages JSON
    utils.ts
  /hooks
    useCalculator.ts
  globals.css
  layout.tsx           ← root layout + AdSense + nav + footer
  page.tsx             ← homepage
5. All Features with Technical Implementation Notes
5.1 Core Mortgage Calculator (Primary Page)
Inputs (shadcn Form + sliders): Home price, down payment (%, $), interest rate, loan term (preset + custom), ZIP code (text input), property tax (annual, auto-estimate), insurance (annual), HOA (monthly), PMI (auto-toggle), loan start date.
Live outputs: Monthly PITI, principal & interest, total interest, payoff date, total payments.
Tabs: Breakdown | Amortization Schedule (360 rows, monthly/yearly toggle, filter) | Extra Payments (lump sum + recurring + bi-weekly) | Charts.
Charts: Balance-over-time line + payment pie (Recharts).
Math: Exported pure functions in lib/formulas.ts (standard mortgage formula + extra payment simulation).
5.2 Additional Calculators
Affordability (income, debts, DTI, front/back-end ratios).
Refinance Savings + Break-Even (compare two loans).
Auto Loan + Personal Loan.
Side-by-Side Comparison (up to 3 scenarios).
Rent vs Buy (integrated tab).
Mortgage Points Buy-Down.
Inflation-Adjusted Toggle (simple CPI multiplier).
Technical Note: Re-use CalculatorForm.tsx + ResultsPanel.tsx with different schema props.
5.3 Unique Free Download Features
PDF Full Report (jsPDF + html2canvas):
Capture entire results section (including charts).
Generate 5–10 page PDF: Cover (logo + inputs), Summary, Breakdown, Full Amortization Table, Charts (as images), Disclaimer.
Button text: “Download Full Professional PDF Report (Free)”.
CSV Export: Full amortization array as downloadable .csv.
Shareable Link: new URLSearchParams(formState) appended to current URL.
Local Scenario Saves: Name + save to localStorage (list + load + delete).
5.4 Shared Delight Features
Dark/Light mode (next-themes).
PWA install prompt.
Print-friendly CSS (@media print).
Keyboard navigation + ARIA labels.
Responsive (mobile-first, Tailwind).
5.5 ZIP / Property Tax Estimator (Client-Side)
Static JSON in lib/taxEstimates.ts (state-level averages + popular ZIP overrides – e.g., { "CA": 0.76, "TX": 1.68, "90210": 0.85 }).
On ZIP change → lookup + auto-fill tax rate field (user can override).
Disclaimer: “Estimate only – actual taxes vary by county/assessment”.
6. Non-Functional Requirements
Performance: Core bundle < 150KB gzipped, First Contentful Paint < 800ms.
SEO: Dynamic metadata per page, Open Graph images, sitemap.xml, robots.txt (Vercel auto).
Accessibility: WCAG 2.2 AA (contrast, focus, screen-reader).
Browser Support: Modern Chrome/Edge/Firefox/Safari + iOS/Android.
Error Handling: Graceful fallbacks for invalid inputs (zod), toast notifications (sonner).
Analytics Tracking: Page views + calculate events + download events (GA4).
7. Monetization Integration
AdSense: Add <Script> in layout.tsx (place 2–3 responsive banners per page – above results, sidebar, below table).
Future Premium: Stripe + Supabase (Month 2).
8. Deployment & CI/CD
Vercel: Connect GitHub repo → auto-deploy on main.
Custom domain: USFinNexus.com (already purchased).
Environment variables: None needed for MVP (add later for Supabase).
9. Testing & Quality
Unit: Formulas + PDF generation.
Component: Forms, charts, downloads.
E2E: Playwright (full user flows + PDF download verification).


